                     <interp inst="t18290115-113-person892" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner never accounted to me for this money, or any part of it; when I sent him out on the 16th, he never returned - I found the book in the barrow which he took his bread out in: I never found him till last Monday evening, when I saw him going into a baker's shop, and took him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I lived with him three weeks and two days.</p>
